[1] Cholera - India (Gujarat)
Date: Wed 1 Oct 2008
Source: Press Trust of India (PTI) [edited]
<http://www.ptinews.com/pti%5Cptisite.nsf/0/F39B638139AFAAA2652574D5003ECE9B?OpenDocument>


A threat of epidemic looms over Valiya taluk [taluk refers to an
administrative subdivision - Mod.LL] here as the district
administration has declared 11 villages as "cholera-infected",
including 1 as the "worst hit".

Vitthalgam village in Valiya taluk has been declared as the 'worst'
hit. While Sadigam, Rajgadh, Choramla, Vandariya, Bhamadiya, Umargam,
Jabugam, Kosyadi, Bharadiya, Holkotar, and Nicoli villages, where a
few patients have been affected by the disease, have been identified
as "cholera-infected," according to a notification issued yesterday
by the District Collector Arti Kanwar.

Sources said 3 teams of health officials headed by the chief district
health officer (CDHO) VD Vegda had visited Vitthalgam and nearby
villages in the last week of September 2008 after numerous cases of
cholera were reported from the area. After thorough assessment of the
areas, the CDHO prepared a detailed report and submitted it to the
collector and based on its recommendation Vitthalgam was declared
worst hit, they added.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The Indian state of Gujarat is in the western aspect of the country
and can be found on a map at
<http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gujarat>. - Mod.LL]

