[11] Cholera - Congo DR (North Kivu)
Date: 30 Sep 2008
Source: Caritas [in French, trans. & summ. JW, edited]

17 dead out of 116 cases of cholera among displaced
---------------------------------------------------
Due to limited access due to insecurity, no humanitarian mission could
go to Ngungu during last week [of 22 Sep 2008], where 116 cases of
cholera have been reported, with 17 dead, among 25,000 displaced
people in the camp located about 60 km west of Goma.

[According to the UN Office for the Coordination of Humanitarian
Affairs (OCHA) in Goma, 12 deaths were reported in Pinga over just
one week in late April 2008, while 159 cases were recorded between 5
and 11 May 2008. -- see ProMED archive 20080602.1764 Cholera,
diarrhea & dysentery update 2008 (27) below. - Mod.JW

North (or Nord) Kivu can be found in northeastern Congo DR on the map at
<http://www.un.org/Depts/Cartographic/map/profile/drcongo.pdf>. - Mod.LL]

